From 1d432d14045771fd5f92dade3bf2b7dc2d1085ad Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ramya Gnanasekar <rgnanase@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Wed, 21 May 2025 10:53:39 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM: CP: wifi: ath12k: Avoid discrepency in ahvif::links_map
 and arvif

ahvif::arvif array is protected by RCU whereas ahvif::links_map is not.
Consider a below scenario during wifi down when link 0,1 getting deleted

CPU 0						CPU 1
ath12k_mac_unassign_link_vif()
	ahvif::arvif -> NULL			CE interrupt
	synchronize_rcu()			ath12k_mac_get_arvif()
	ahvif::links_map->old value			ahvif::links_map->old_value
							rcu_redereference(arvif)

When arvif is dereferenced in CPU 1, arvif is already assigned to NULL.
But ahvif::links_map still holds old bitmap.
Fix this by updating the bitmap first and then assign the arvif pointer
to NULL.

Call trace during wifi down:
